            "answer_text": "People in the ancient world did not have as many changes of clothing as we do now, and sometimes outer garments were not easily washable, By wearing a layer of cloth between their bodies and their outer garment, they kept the latter from absorbing sweat and dirt from the body, keeping it cleaner and helping it last much longer. This tradition persisted to the middle of last century, when men typically wore undershirts and women full slips, to protect their outer garments. ",
